Good food, but terrible service experience

The food here is really good, and kudos to the chef for preparing such delicious dishes.

However, the service left a lot to be desired. In the middle of my meal, the staff (a lady) asked me to get up and repark my car, even though there were no signs indicating where parking was or wasnâ€™t allowed.

It was frustrating and completely disrupted the dining experience.

The food deserves a better service team, and I hope they improve their customer handling in the future.

In short - Mixed experience.

Food - Good no complaints

Service - I don't remember exactly but there was some thing on this front that didn't go well.

Ambience -  Excellent. Most stars for this .

Review -

Good food but it's been a while I don't remember why it was not exactly a pleasant experience. I loved the ambience though.

I chanced upon this hidden gem while on a short visit to Goa. Located really close to Dabolim airport this place takes you to another realm due to its design sense and green vegetation.
The first impression was wow what a place.

The next wow wow happened when we tasted the food.
This is a place you can spend hours chilling and enjoying the vibe and cuisine. They serve continental and Asian menu. Known for excellent Baos.
